brawler.name: Crow
brawler.description: Crow trusts no one and keeps to himself. The most anyone knows about him is that he's often found at the diner, hanging out with Bull and Bibi.

brawler.name: Mortis
brawler.description: Mortis had grand designs built around being a mortician and a vampire, but the fact that nobody is dying at Starr Park has put a huge damper on his plans.
brawler.attackDescription: Mortis dashes forward with a sharp swing of his shovel, creating business opportunities for himself. When he has all three dashes ready, he'll gain a longer dash after a short delay.
brawler.superDescription: Mortis calls forth a swarm of vampire bats that drain the health of his enemies while restoring his. Creepy!

gadgets.gadget1Description: Mortis spins his shovel, hitting all enemies around himself for 1880 damage.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Mortis reaps the life essence of a Brawler he defeats, restoring 20% of his max health.
starPowers.starPowers2Description: Mortis gains his longer dash 2 seconds faster.

brawler.name: El Primo
brawler.description: El Primo is always in the spotlight and that's right where he wants to be! There's no audience he can't win over, except maybe his fellow performers...
brawler.attackDescription: El Primo fires off a furious flurry of four fiery fists. That's a spicy jalapeno knuckle sandwich!
brawler.superDescription: Leaping high, El Primo drops an Intergalactic Elbow that knocks around enemies and destroys cover!

hypercharge.hyperchargeDescription: El Primo drops an Intergalactic Elbow that brings enemies to the Epicenter.

gadgets.gadget1Description: El Primo grabs the closest enemy within his reach and flips them like a pancake over his broad shoulders.
gadgets.gadget2Description: El Primo summons a small meteor to strike the nearest enemy. It deals 2880 damage and destroys walls.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Enemies caught in El Primo's Super will burn for 1786 damage over 4 seconds.
starPowers.starPowers2Description: El Primo gains a 25% speed boost for 4.0 seconds after using his Super.

brawler.name: Dynamike
brawler.description: Dynamike is an old miner and prospector who's become obsessed with explosions. Nothing makes him happier than a big boom!
brawler.attackDescription: Mike tosses two sticks of dynamite, passing over any obstacles in the way. The fuses are cut as short as Mike's explosive temper!
brawler.superDescription: A big-bada-barrel of dynamite blows up cover. Any surviving enemies get knocked back on impact!

gadgets.gadget1Description: Dynamike spins furiously with increased movement speed and throws multiple sticks of dynamite around himself. Each dynamite deals 2400 damage to enemies.
gadgets.gadget2Description: Once activated, the next main attack also stuns enemies for 1.5 seconds.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Dynamike can ride the blast wave of his explosives to jump over obstacles!

brawler.name: Nita
brawler.description: Nita is a ferocious child who never backs down from a fight! The teddy bear on her head serves as a warning to others: don't poke the bear.
brawler.attackDescription: Nita sends forth a shockwave, damaging enemies caught in the tremor.
brawler.superDescription: Nita summons the spirit of Big Baby Bear to hunt down her enemies.

gadgets.gadget1Description: Nita commands her bear to slam the ground, stunning all enemies within its reach.
gadgets.gadget2Description: For the next 3 seconds, Nita's bear gets a 35% shield against damage.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Nita recovers 1040 health whenever her bear hits an enemy brawler. When Nita deals damage to an enemy brawler, her bear regains 1040 health.
starPowers.starPowers2Description: Nita's bear attacks faster. Time between swipes is reduced by 60%.

brawler.name: Jessie
brawler.description: Jessie is a prodigy who builds guns and gadgets from parts she finds in the junkyard. Maybe one day her mother Pam will see she can fend for herself!
brawler.attackDescription: Jessie fires off an energy orb. After hitting a target the orb bounces to the next target in range, hitting up to three enemies. Each bounce deals 25% less damage.
brawler.superDescription: Jessie deploys a gun turret that automatically shoots at enemies. It's made of 100% recycled materials!

hypercharge.hyperchargeDescription: Jessie's turret has 50% more health and deals 20% more damage.

gadgets.gadget1Description: Jessie triggers a shockwave from her turret, slowing down all enemies within its area of effect.
gadgets.gadget2Description: Scrappy's attack speed is doubled for 5.0 seconds.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Jessie can repair her gun turret for 1060 of its missing health by zapping it with her attack.
starPowers.starPowers2Description: Scrappy the Turret now shoots energy orbs that bounce between enemies. The orbs' range after a bounce is 51% of normal range.

brawler.name: Barley
brawler.description: A bartending robot designed to mix drinks and banter with patrons, Barley also makes sure to keep his bar clean, to the detriment of anyone who makes a mess.
brawler.attackDescription: Barley lobs a bottle, breaking it on the ground. Enemies take damage from the splash, and more damage over time if they stay in the puddle.
brawler.superDescription: Barley hurls a flurry of fiery bottles, covering a huge area in flames. This one's on the house!

gadgets.gadget1Description: Barley drops a sticky concoction that leaves a puddle, slowing down all enemies that makes contact with it.
gadgets.gadget2Description: Barley throws a healing potion at nearby allies that creates an area that heals for 720 health per second.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Barley regains 480 health from each attack.
starPowers.starPowers2Description: Adds +200 damage per second to Barley's attack.

brawler.name: Spike
brawler.description: Most people think Spike is Colt and Shelly's cute sidekick at the Ranger Ranch. Nobody could begin to guess the depths of his trauma.
brawler.attackDescription: Spike fires off a small cactus that explodes, shooting spikes in different directions.
brawler.superDescription: Spike lobs a thorny grenade. Enemies caught in the blast area take damage and are slowed down.

gadgets.gadget1Description: Spike shoots 3 waves of needles in all directions, dealing 1120 damage per hit.
gadgets.gadget2Description: Spike grows a large cactus with 2400 health to give cover to friendlies. If destroyed, the cactus bursts, and all nearby friendlies recover 1440 health.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: After using Super, Spike regenerates 1200 health per second by staying in its area of effect.
starPowers.starPowers2Description: Spikes from the cactus grenade fly in a curving motion, making it easier to hit targets.

brawler.name: Rico
brawler.description: Rico is definitely a real space bounty hunter who tracks down the galaxy's most wanted criminals, not a gumball machine pretending to be cool.
brawler.attackDescription: Rico's bullets bounce off walls, gaining range. They can hit enemies behind cover.
brawler.superDescription: Rico fires a long burst of bullets that pierce through enemies and bounce off walls, gaining range.

gadgets.gadget1Description: Rico blasts waves of bouncy bullets in all directions.
gadgets.gadget2Description: Rico's next attack will heal him for 256 health from each bounce of a projectile.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Rico's bullets, from attack and Super alike, get supercharged by their first bounce and deal +256 damage!
starPowers.starPowers2Description: When Rico falls below 40% health, he runs 34% faster!

brawler.name: Brock
brawler.description: Brock is a smack-talking video game enthusiast. His big attitude hides a more introverted personality, but he'll still do whatever it takes to win!
brawler.attackDescription: Brock lets fly with a single Rockin' Rocket that really goes the distance.
brawler.superDescription: Brock fires a rocket barrage that takes out enemies and obstacles. He only wants to see you bathing in the Rocket Rain!

gadgets.gadget1Description: Brock blasts the ground below him and propels himself into the air. The explosion deals 580 damage to nearby enemies.
gadgets.gadget2Description: Brock's next attack is a mega rocket that is bigger, badder, faster and destroys walls.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Rocket Rain now rains down 44% more rockets.
starPowers.starPowers2Description: Brock loads a fourth rocket into his launcher, increasing his ammo capacity (and discarding the thermos bottle he's been keeping in his launcher's #4 tube).

brawler.name: Bull
brawler.description: Bull isn't as carefree as he was in his youth, but just because his rowdy days are behind him doesn't mean he won't still crush someone who's asking for it.
brawler.attackDescription: Bull's double-barreled shotgun deals heavy damage. It has very short range, so Bull likes to get up close and personal.
brawler.superDescription: Bull puts his head down and bulldozes through opponents and obstacles. He's always been headstrong!

gadgets.gadget1Description: Bull instantly rejuvenates himself for 2000 health.
gadgets.gadget2Description: Bull can interrupt his Super charge and slow all nearby opponents with a massive stomp for 1.5 seconds.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: When Bull falls below 60% health, his reload speed doubles!
starPowers.starPowers2Description: When Bull falls below 40% health, he gains a shield that reduces all damage he takes by 30%.

brawler.name: Colt
brawler.description: Colt is the star attraction at Starr Park! His good looks, charisma and gun twirling tricks win over any audience, except maybe Shelly.
brawler.attackDescription: Colt shoots six straight long-range shots out of his revolvers.
brawler.superDescription: Colt rattles off a massive burst of bullets that shoot extra far and destroy cover.

gadgets.gadget2Description: Colt's next attack is a powerful shot that deals as much damage as 2 of his regular bullets, while going through obstacles and opponents alike.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Colt's movement speed is increased by 13%.
starPowers.starPowers2Description: Colt's attack range and bullet speed are increased by 11%.

brawler.name: Shelly
brawler.description: Shelly's the perfect ranger: reliable, tough, and terrific with her shotgun. She never understood why Colt got to steal the limelight...
brawler.attackDescription: Shelly's boomstick fires a wide spread of pellets to a medium range. The more pellets hit, the greater the damage.
brawler.superDescription: Shelly's Super Shell obliterates both cover and enemies. Any survivors get knocked back.

gadgets.gadget1Description: Shelly dashes ahead, skipping a few unnecessary steps!
gadgets.gadget2Description: On activation, for the next 5 seconds Shelly's main attacks focuses the fire to a smaller area with an increased range.

starPowers.starPowers1Description: Shelly's Super shells slow down enemies for 2 seconds!
starPowers.starPowers2Description: When Shelly falls below 40% health, she instantly heals for 2220 health. Band-Aid recharges in 15 seconds.
